sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: DT Cloud Star Acquisition adjourns shareholder meeting to December 22 By Investing.com
feed.summary: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corp has announced the adjournment of its extraordinary general meeting of shareholders to December 22, 2025, at 10:00 AM Eastern Time. Shareholders wishing to change or revoke their votes must do so by December 21, 2025, at 11:59 PM ET. The company also recently approved amendments to extend the deadline for a business combination and appointed Dr. Xunyong Zhou as a director.

feed.title: DT Cloud Star Adjourns Shareholder Meeting to December 22
feed.summary: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corporation (DTSQ) has adjourned its extraordinary general meeting of shareholders to December 22, 2025. The meeting was originally held on December 15, 2025, but no business was conducted except for the adjournment approval. Shareholders can now change or revoke their votes, or withdraw redemption requests, until December 21, 2025.

feed.title: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corp Adjourns Extraordinary General Meeting
feed.summary: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corp announced the adjournment of its extraordinary general meeting to December 22, 2025, at 10:00 AM ET. Shareholders can modify or revoke their votes until December 21, 2025, and may withdraw redemption requests by contacting VStock Transfer. Advantage Proxy has been retained for proxy solicitation.

feed.title: DT Cloud Faces Nasdaq Delisting After Compliance Denial
feed.summary: DT Cloud, a Chinese business-to-business platform, is facing delisting from Nasdaq after its appeal concerning a share price non-compliance notice was denied. The company's appeal for its American Depositary Shares (ADS) to remain listed was rejected by an independent Nasdaq hearings panel, with delisting set to take effect on December 11, 2024. DT Cloud can pursue further review with the Nasdaq Listing and Hearing Review Council, but its ADS will continue trading over-the-counter during any such process.

feed.title: DT Cloud Faces Nasdaq Delisting After Compliance Denial
feed.summary: DT Cloud Stock will be delisted from the Nasdaq Capital Market due to its failure to regain compliance with the exchange's shareholder equity requirement. The company's appeal for continued listing was denied by the Nasdaq Hearings Panel, and trading of its ordinary shares will be suspended at the opening of business on December 10, 2024.

feed.title: DT Cloud Star Acquisition appoints Dr. Xunyong Zhou as director
feed.summary: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corp has appointed Dr. Xunyong Zhou to its board of directors. Dr. Zhou brings over six years of experience in biotechnology and health innovation, focusing on enzyme-based solutions and cell therapy technologies. The company, trading as DTSQ, has seen recent shareholder approvals for business combination extensions and a non-redemption agreement.

feed.title: DT Cloud Faces Nasdaq Delisting After Compliance Denial
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corp. (DYCQ) is facing delisting from the Nasdaq Global Market after its request for continued listing was denied. Nasdaq informed the company on August 25, 2025, that it did not meet the publicly held shares requirement, and despite a submitted compliance plan, Nasdaq decided on November 12, 2025, to deny the request. Trading of DYCQ stock will be suspended on November 21, 2025, unless an appeal is successfully made.

feed.title: Nasdaq to suspend DT Cloud Acquisition trading after listing rule non-compliance
feed.summary: Nasdaq will suspend trading of DT Cloud Acquisition Corp (NASDAQ:DYCQ) after the company failed to comply with listing rules, specifically the publicly held shares requirement. Despite submitting a plan to regain compliance, Nasdaq determined the company did not meet several requirements. DT Cloud Acquisition's various securities are currently listed, but delisting will proceed if no appeal is filed.

feed.title: DT Cloud Acquisition Corp. Delays 10-Q Filing
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corp. has announced a delay in filing its Form 10-Q for the financial period ending September 30, 2025, due to difficulties in finalizing financial results. The company expects to file the report within five calendar days of the original due date and does not anticipate significant financial changes compared to the prior year.

feed.title: DT Cloud Faces Nasdaq Delisting After Compliance Denial
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corp. (DYCQ) is facing delisting from the Nasdaq Global Market after failing to meet the public shares requirement for continued listing. Despite submitting a compliance plan, Nasdaq denied their request, and trading of the company's stock is set to be suspended on November 21, 2025, unless an appeal is made and granted.

feed.title: DT Cloud Star (DTSQ) extends deadline; first $75,000 deposit made
feed.summary: DT Cloud Star Acquisition Corporation (DTSQ) filed an 8-K/A to correct a clerical error and confirm shareholder approval for extending its business combination deadline from October 26, 2025, to October 26, 2026. This extension requires a $75,000 deposit into the trust account for each month, and the company has already made its initial deposit to extend the deadline to November 26, 2025, funded by an unsecured promissory note to its sponsor. Shareholders also approved director elections, auditor ratification, and amendments to the company's memorandum and articles of association.

feed.title: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation Announces Change of Extraordinary General Meeting Date
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation announced that its Extraordinary General Meeting (EGM), previously scheduled for May 21, 2025, has been postponed to May 23, 2025. The redemption right deadline has also been moved to May 21, 2025, while the record date for the EGM remains April 30, 2025. Shareholders who have already submitted their proxy and do not wish to change their vote do not need to take further action.

feed.title: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation Announces Change of Extraordinary General Meeting Date
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation announced that its Extraordinary General Meeting (EGM), originally scheduled for April 18, 2025, has been postponed to April 23, 2025. The redemption right deadline has also been moved to April 21, 2025, while the EGM record date remains March 31, 2025. No changes were made to the proposals for shareholder voting.

feed.title: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation Signs Letter of Intent for a Business Combination
feed.summary: DT Cloud Acquisition Corporation announced that it has signed a non-binding letter of intent for a business combination with Shanghai Maius Pharmaceutical Technology Co., LTD. Shanghai Maius is a biopharmaceutical R&D company specializing in innovative formulations and targeted small-molecule chemical drugs. The definitive agreement is expected in the fourth quarter of 2024, subject to due diligence, approvals, and other customary conditions.
